    <!-- Performance -->
    <div class="exhibition-detail-body" style="margin-top: 2.5rem;">
      <h2 style="font-size: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Performance: "With the Shield or on the Shield"</h2>
      <p>The opening performance by Weronika Wysocka (2025) explored the evolution of creative consciousness. The artist functioned as a medium through which time, history, and memory flow. She guided audiences through historical contexts, emotional artistic states, archetypes, ethos, and creator roles across different periods, revealing transformations in how artists function within art worlds and broader society.</p>
      <p>The artist utilized handcrafted objects—a surrealist clock shield and hand spiral scepter—as tools for transitioning between temporal and corporeal states.</p>
      <p><a href="https://weronikawysocka.com/works/with-the-shield-or-on-the-shield" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: #a08040; text-decoration: underline;">View performance details →</a></p>
